radiative transfer model that includes the effects of ionization. The\ndata are consistent with a clear atmosphere between $\\sim$1--100 mbar which\nestablish a lower limit on Na at 0.4$^{+2}_{-0.3}$ ppm\n([Na/H]=-0.64$^{+0.78}_{-0.6}$), consistent with solar. However, we can not\nrule out the presence of clouds at $\\sim$10 mbar which allow for higher Na\nabundances which would be consistent with stellar metallicity measured for the\nhost star ([Na/H]=0.485$\\pm$0.043).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Nov 2018 22:21:18 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 4 Jan 2019 18:26:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-07"}
