 for\nfast-rotating stars, and find that our measurements are smaller by more than\none order of magnitude. The model developed using the V-band photometry as a\nconstraint was applied to several other observables. Overall, the results of\nthis multi-technique study were very positive, with a good match for multi-band\nphotometry, polarization, and most spectroscopic characteristics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 6 Nov 2018 07:32:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-11-07"}
